4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT PROVIDING FOR CITIZEN PARTICIPATION IN FURTHERANCE
5 OF ARTICLE II, SECTION 8, OF THE MONTANA CONSTITUTION WHEN THE ATTORNEY GENERAL
6 SEEKS TO ENGAGE IN LITIGATION IN WHICH THE STATE MAY HAVE AN INTEREST; PROVIDING
7 NOTICE WHEN THE ATTORNEY GENERAL INTENDS TO ENGAGE IN LITIGATION IN WHICH THE STATE
8 MAY HAVE AN INTEREST; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION; REQUIRING A PUBLIC HEARING AND PUBLIC
9 COMMENT ON THE ATTORNEY GENERAL'S INTENT TO ENGAGE IN LITIGATION IN WHICH THE STATE
10 MAY HAVE AN INTEREST; REQUIRING THE ATTORNEY GENERAL TAKE UNDER CONSIDERATION AND
11 RESPOND TO PUBLIC COMMENTS AFTER A PUBLIC HEARING; REQUIRING A PROJECTION OF
12 LITIGATION COSTS AND REPORTING OF ACTUAL LITIGATION COSTS; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AND
13 AMENDING SECTION 2-15-501, MCA.”
14
15 WHEREAS, Article II, section 8, of the Montana Constitution provides that the "public has the right to
16 expect governmental agencies to afford such reasonable opportunity for citizen participation in the operation of
17 the agencies prior to the final decision as may be provided by law"; and
18 WHEREAS, Article VI, section 4, of the Montana Constitution provides the Attorney General "shall have
19 the duties and powers provided by law"; and
20 WHEREAS, the Attorney General currently has broad authority to litigate matters in the name of the
21 State of Montana in which the state has an interest pursuant to section 2-15-501, MCA; and
22 WHEREAS, the public currently has no opportunity to provide input or public comment as to whether
23 the litigation furthers the interests of the State of Montana or not; and
24 WHEREAS, there are few checks on the spending of government funds to pursue the litigation and
25 ensure that it is in the interests of the State of Montana; and
26 WHEREAS, providing for public comment and public participation in executive branch decisions
27 strengthens democracy and trust in government; and
28 WHEREAS, the Montana Supreme Court has held that the Attorney General's authority may be
