8 (v) As used in this subsection (1)(b), the following definitions apply:
9 (A) "Attorney general" means the attorney general, any subordinates, or any agency litigation in the
10 department of justice.
11 (B) "Engaging in litigation" means filing or joining in litigation as a party, filing a brief in a pending
12 proceeding because of strong interest in the subject matter, or providing funding or personnel to support the
13 litigation.
14 (2) to represent the state in all bankruptcy proceedings in which the state's interest may be
15 affected and in other debt collection proceedings at the request of a state agency;
16 (3) after judgment in any of the causes referred to in subsections (1) and (2), to direct the issuing
17 of a process as may be necessary to carry the judgment into execution;
18 (4) to keep a permanent register of all cases prosecuted or defended by the attorney general.
19 Each case under subsection (1) must be entered into the register on commencement of the litigation and
20 updated within 30 days of the conclusion of litigation in the matter. The update at the conclusion of litigation
21 must include an itemization of costs associated with the litigation for each case, including but not limited to fees
22 and expenses for outside counsel and the number of hours expended in the matter by in-house counsel. The
23 register must be open to the inspection of the public during business hours. The attorney general shall deliver
24 the register to the attorney general's successor in office.
25 (5) to exercise supervisory powers over county attorneys in all matters pertaining to the duties of
